According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Cartilage Regeneration Technology Market was valued at USD 1.45 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 1.58 billion in 2026 to USD 2.87 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 7.8% during the forecast period. The market is expanding steadily due to the rising prevalence of osteoarthritis, increasing sports-related injuries, and growing demand for advanced regenerative therapies that restore joint function while reducing the need for joint replacement surgeries. Continuous innovation in tissue engineering, stem cell therapies, and biomaterial scaffolds is further accelerating market growth.
